Sandbox control and observability - Get detailed sandbox metrics and logs.

Each sandbox can be observed in the Cloudflare dashboard, sandbox logs can be queried or shipped to external providers like Datadog or Splunk, and the control plane ships with a built-in UI, making it easy to track the state of sandboxes or SSH into specific machines.

Just add the relevant binding in wrangler config, write a zod definition, and short function in custom-tools.js :

 defineTool({
 name: "r2_host_file",
 description: "Upload from sandbox to R2 and get a public URL.",
 inputSchema: z.object({
 key: z.string().describe("Object key"),
 content: z.string().describe("UTF-8 file body"),
 contentType: z.string().describe("MIME type"),
 }),
 run: async ({ key, content, contentType }, { env }) => {
 await env.PUBLIC_BUCKET.put(
 key, content, { httpMetadata: { contentType }}
 );
 return `${env.PUB_R2_URL.replace(/\/$/, "")}/${encodeURI(key)}`;
 }
}), 
